{"id":14881095,"mediaExerciseId":"715a2fc1-9bb9-407b-9b0d-89a57209282c","exerciseName":"7","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612315,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":238,"solutions":[{"id":6027371,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **Renata needs help to understand the positive protective covenants.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":62,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/ea79f3c082ec195bc17c0c68bb0b73b5/88f4cf2efb0bfcd54c2df181e276cb0a/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":31,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/ea79f3c082ec195bc17c0c68bb0b73b5/88f4cf2efb0bfcd54c2df181e276cb0a/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"A protective covenant is one of the elements of indenture or other debt agreements. A protective covenant is a limitation that does not allow the debtor to take risky activities and put the company in a dangerous position. This limitation protects the lender and helps him receive the money-back.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/ea79f3c082ec195bc17c0c68bb0b73b5/7f5702da042c7732dc5ccc30f9868778/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/ea79f3c082ec195bc17c0c68bb0b73b5/7f5702da042c7732dc5ccc30f9868778/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"There are two types of those covenants: what the debtor should do (positive) and what the debtor should not (negative).\n\n- An example of a positive protective covenant is that the firm must keep a minimum level of capital.\n\n- Another example of positive protective covenants can be the required minimum level of working capital.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":218,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/ea79f3c082ec195bc17c0c68bb0b73b5/c710ee0ac3b5aab1fbbf11f48fe3a96d/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/ea79f3c082ec195bc17c0c68bb0b73b5/c710ee0ac3b5aab1fbbf11f48fe3a96d/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**This feature makes the bondholders protected, and it lowers the coupon rate. But if the company accepts this feature, the company will have a prohibition to do many activities. So, the management of the company can not do what they want if it is too risky activities.**\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/ea79f3c082ec195bc17c0c68bb0b73b5/9b2c55bdb23feb988cc06cf51ec3fef6/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/ea79f3c082ec195bc17c0c68bb0b73b5/9b2c55bdb23feb988cc06cf51ec3fef6/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"bd24d00f-d248-4991-8e44-25e66df31e4d","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","